# =============================================================================
# File: /opt/ansible-k3s-cluster/README.cluster-lifecycle-map
# =============================================================================
# Purpose:
#   Provide a complete lifecycle map for the cluster, from kernel build to
#   deployment, verification, rollback, and long-term maintenance.
#
# Lifecycle Stages:
#
#   1. Build
#      - Builder compiles kernel
#
#   2. Verify
#      - Artifact checks
#      - Dependency checks
#
#   3. Deploy
#      - Ansible rollout
#      - Node-by-node update
#
#   4. Validate
#      - Diagnostics suite
#      - k3s workload checks
#
#   5. Operate
#      - Daily/weekly/monthly runbook tasks
#
#   6. Recover
#      - Rollback strategy
#      - Incident response
#
#   7. Improve
#      - Capacity planning
#      - Maturity model
#
# Notes:
#   - This file defines the authoritative lifecycle for the entire system.
# =============================================================================
